cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper presents a new architecture for sequence modeling that outperforms current state-of-the-art methods on language modeling tasks. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the arXiv sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper leverages connections between recurrent and convolutional models, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
